com.bluegosling.apt.reflect

Class ArTypeParameter<D extends ArGenericDeclaration>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bluegosling.apt.reflect.ArTypeParameter<D>
  • Type Parameters:
    D - the type of element that declared the type parameter
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ArAnnotatedConstruct, ArAnnotatedElement

    public class ArTypeParameter<D extends ArGenericDeclaration>
extends Object
    A type parameter declaration. Type parameters can be declared on generic classes, interfaces, methods, and constructors. This class represents the declaration of the type parameter. Uses of it generic types are represented by ArTypeVariable (using similar terminology as TypeParameterElement and TypeVariable.
    See Also:
    TypeVariable, TypeParameterElement

      • getBounds

        public List<? extends ArType> getBounds()
        Returns the upper bounds (aka "extends" bounds) for this type variable. For example in the declaration Interface<T extends SomeClass & Cloneable & Serializable>, the type variable T has three bounds: SomeClass, Cloneable, and Serializable. If a type variable has no bounds defined then the implicit upper bound is java.lang.Object.
        Returns:
        the upper bounds for this type variable

      • getGenericDeclaration

        public D getGenericDeclaration()
        Returns the declaration for this type variable. This will be either a Class, ArMethod, or ArConstructor, depending on where the type variable was declared.

        If the type variable is a captured wildcard then this method returns null.

        Returns:
        the generic declaration that declared this type variable

      • getName

        public String getName()
        Returns the name of the type variable. For example, in an interface declared as Interface<T>, the one type variable's name is T.
        Returns:
        the name of the type variable
